  "prompt": "I have 3 weeks of free time, what should I do?",
  "response": "Okay, 3 weeks of free time is a fantastic opportunity! To give you the best suggestions, I need a little more information about you and what you're looking for.  Tell me a bit about:\n\n**1. Your Interests & Goals:**\n\n*   **What do you enjoy doing?**  (e.g., reading, being outdoors, learning new skills, being creative, socializing, relaxing, being productive, traveling)\n*   **What are you hoping to get out of this free time?** (e.g., relaxation, adventure, personal growth, productivity, skill development, making memories)\n*   **Are there any specific things you've always wanted to try or learn?**\n*   **Do you want to be productive, or do you want to be lazy?**\n\n**2. Your Budget:**\n\n*   **How much money are you willing to spend?** (e.g., nothing, a little, a moderate amount, a lot)\n*   **Are you willing to travel?** If so, what is your budget for travel?\n\n**3. Your Location & Mobility:**\n\n*   **Where are you located?** (General area, like \"Midwest USA\" or \"London, UK\" is fine) This helps with location-specific suggestions.\n*   **Do you have access to a car?**\n*   **Are you willing/able to travel far?**\n\n**4. Your Social Preferences:**\n\n*   **Do you want to spend time alone, with friends/family, or a mix?**\n*   **Are you looking to meet new people?**\n\n**Once I have this information, I can give you much more tailored and helpful suggestions!**\n\nIn the meantime, here are some general ideas to get you thinking:\n\n**Relaxation & Rejuvenation:**\n\n*   **Staycation:** Explore your local area like a tourist. Visit museums, parks, restaurants, and attractions you've never been to.\n*   **Reading Challenge:** Devote time to reading books you've been meaning to get to.\n*   **Spa Days:** Treat yourself to massages, facials, or other spa treatments.\n*   **Mindfulness & Meditation:** Practice daily meditation and mindfulness exercises to reduce stress.\n*   **Catch Up on Sleep:** Prioritize getting enough sleep to recharge.\n*   **Digital Detox:** Unplug from technology for a few days or even a week.\n\n**Learning & Skill Development:**\n\n*   **Online Courses:** Learn a new skill through platforms like Coursera, Udemy, Skillshare, or edX.\n*   **Language Learning:** Start learning a new language with apps like Duolingo or Babbel.\n*   **Creative Writing:** Try writing a short story, poem, or even start a novel.\n*   **Photography:** Learn the basics of photography and practice taking pictures.\n*   **Coding:** Learn a new programming language.\n*   **DIY Projects:** Tackle home improvement or crafting projects.\n*   **Start a Blog or YouTube Channel:** Share your thoughts and creations with the world.\n\n**Adventure & Exploration:**\n\n*   **Road Trip:** Plan a road trip to explore a new region.\n*   **Camping/Hiking:** Spend time in nature with camping or hiking trips.\n*   **Volunteer Travel:** Combine travel with volunteering for a cause you care about.\n*   **Visit National Parks:** Explore the natural beauty of national parks.\n*   **Go backpacking:** If you're feeling adventurous.\n*   **Try a new sport:** Go skydiving, surfing, rock climbing or something else adrenaline-pumping.\n\n**Productivity & Personal Growth:**\n\n*   **Declutter & Organize:** Declutter your home and organize your belongings.\n*   **Personal Finance:** Review your finances and create a budget.\n*   **Volunteer:** Give back to your community by volunteering your time.\n*   **Networking:** Attend industry events or connect with professionals in your field.\n*   **Start a Side Hustle:** Explore ways to earn extra income through freelancing or online businesses.\n*   **Set Goals:** Set some tangible goals and spend time completing some of the beginning steps.\n\n**Social & Fun:**\n\n*   **Host Parties:** Plan gatherings with friends and family.\n*   **Game Nights:** Organize game nights with board games or video games.\n*   **Attend Concerts or Shows:** See your favorite artists or discover new ones.\n*   **Join a Club or Group:** Connect with people who share your interests.\n*   **Go out with friends:** Go to bars, restaurants, clubs, festivals or activities with friends.\n\n**I'm excited to hear more about your preferences so I can provide more specific recommendations!**\n",
